<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1576,1891]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1576,1603]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Comments.</emphasis>
Broun based this species on two specimens, one of which was in the BMNH and is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,1613,1639]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">lectotype</typeStatus>
to stabilise the epithet. This species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1886" box="[865,1017,1613,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Caccomolpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[865,1017,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Caccomolpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the form of the subcoxal lines on abdominal ventrite 1 which are convex and form a broad axillary space. This species is considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1886" box="[258,520,1685,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Caccomolpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">
<emphasis box="[258,520,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Caccomolpus globosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by M. Daccordi (pers. obs.), but a full revision of the species is needed before formal synonymy is actioned.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
